description: For sale: $575,000. This dazzling 3 bedroom 3 bath retreat on 5 acres is perfectly located close to town but still retains an idlylic location that will amaze you! All the work has been completed for you...just move in. The main floor includes a gorgeous sunroom off of the stunning kitchen featuring knotty alder cabinets w/stainless steel appliances, granite backsplash, countertops & island w/breakfast bar, spacious living room with fireplace and master suite has a beautifully tiled walk-in shower and jetted tub. The lower level has 2 more generous sized bedrooms, family w/fireplace, laundry area, full bath, large storage area. From every room you will be impressed with views of the countryside. Outside you will find plenty of room to relax or entertain. There is a deck that runs the length of the house & also a covered patio. Along with the 2 car attached garage you also have a detached shed/workshop. With plenty of trees, wildlife and a field of flowers. This tranquil piece of paradise won't last long!

description: For sale: $483,500. Exceptional home located on 1.76 acres walkout lot that is beautifully landscaped.  Main floor living at it's best!  An open floor plan that is perfect for entertaining.  The main floor Master suite has a large walk in closet, attached sun room with new windows and you have access to deck to enjoy the views.  Landscaping has been updated so you can see the beautiful surroundings.  This home features both a heated shed/work shop & a large pole barn for your toys.  The walkout lower level has 2 guest rooms, large family room with a  wet bar, an exercise room & plenty of storage. Seller has installed new windows in the sun room, new well pump, new pressure tank, and new furnace/air conditioning in 2019.   A $3000.00 allowance is included for updating the living room flooring. Come and see your forever home!

description: For sale: $359,900. Absolutely stunning home located on a cul-de-sac St in the Jewel. Inviting & open main floor. Beautiful custom kitchen featuring white cabinetry, walk-in pantry, large center island w/pendant lighting, tiled backsplash & stainless appliances. Spacious dinette space leads to the large aggregate stone patio (14x27). Family room w/vaulted ceilings, ceiling fan, accent wall, hardwood flooring & today's modern electric fireplace w/oversized windows which lets light flow in. Full bath w/hardwood flooring, wall sconces & custom vanity. Master suite features ceiling fan, large walk-in closet, 3/4 walk-in tiled shower, tile floors, and his & her sinks. 2nd bed has french doors. Additional features include: LP siding, sprinkler system, white painted doors & trim, recessed lighting, fully finished garage w/floor drain and in floor heat in garage & home. Come enjoy all this beautiful home has to offer and enjoy the oversized yard w/wildlife, easy access to town & the beautiful Jewel Golf Course.
For sale: $199,000. Perfect home to start and/or grow your family! Features massive master bedroom, finished basement living space, fenced yard, and new flooring throughout.

description: Recently sold: $262,000. This is a beautiful split level home within walking distance of Bluffview Elementary waiting for its new family.  On the main floor the kitchen, living room and living room have an open floor plan and brand new oak hardwood floors.  The kitchen has stainless steel appliances and granite countertops.  The large master bedroom with a 3/4 master bath, 2 more bedrooms and a full bath make up the rest of the main floor.  The spacious basement has a large bedroom, full bath, laundry room and a huge family room.  There is a porch off the front of the house and a large 2 tier deck in the backyard.  Half of the backyard is fenced, there is also a firepit and a large barn style shed with a loft.  The house is complete with a 2 car garage.  Jump on this amazing home cuz it well be gone quick!

description:
Recently sold: $111,000. *Willing to pay 2% commission to buyer's agents.*

Across the street from high school and 5 minutes from elementary school and hospital. Bus to Rochester Mayo Clinic runs nearby.

description: For sale: $327,000. Single family home in Pepin Lodge has well established HOA and outstanding amenities including large, in ground heated swimming pool, great sandy beachfront with rights to use the "day dock", meticulous lawncare and landscaping, and snow removal in the winter. This unit has 3 very nice views of Lake Pepin. Inside this unit you'll see a very well cared for home with a modern floorplan, fireplace and wood stove, walkout lower level and a great deck for entertaining. If you've been looking for a smaller, beautiful, outdoor oriented town to re-locate, retire or vacation at, make sure to come see Minnesota's beautiful "South Shore"!

description: For sale: $483,500. Exceptional home located on 1.76 acres walkout lot that is beautifully landscaped.  Main floor living at it's best!  An open floor plan that is perfect for entertaining.  The main floor Master suite has a large walk in closet, attached sun room with new windows and you have access to deck to enjoy the views.  Landscaping has been updated so you can see the beautiful surroundings.  This home features both a heated shed/work shop & a large pole barn for your toys.  The walkout lower level has 2 guest rooms, large family room with a  wet bar, an exercise room & plenty of storage. Seller has installed new windows in the sun room, new well pump, new pressure tank, and new furnace/air conditioning in 2019.   A $3000.00 allowance is included for updating the living room flooring. Come and see your forever home!

description:
Recently sold: $345,000. High-end colonial style home situated on an one acre lot in the desirable and deed-restricted Eagle Vista Estates neighborhood. Beautiful wooded surroundings and breathtaking bluff views. Minutes from Lake Pepin, walking trails, Rochester, and Red Wing. 

This luxury home features high-end finishes throughout, including Brazilian Cherry wood flooring, granite counter-tops, elite stainless steel appliances, two fireplaces, integrated speakers, a 400 square foot recreation room wired for tech, and a 500 square foot master suite.

description: Recently sold: $208,000. Beautiful ground level condo w/gorgeous panoramic views of Lake Pepin! Private master suite and living room open onto a large patio that runs the whole front of the condo w/ lots of room for outdoor entertaining. Custom Kitchen W/Stainless Steel Appliances & maple cabinets, Gas fireplace, tile floors, extra storage room, & heated parking. Shared exercise room, library & gathering room. Just a short walk to the Harbor, shops & restaurants! A Must See!

description: Recently sold: $140,000. Charming 3 Bedroom, 2 Bath Home. Hardwood floors throughout most of the house. Newer Maple Kitchen & Dining Room. Spacious rooms.
